Another advantage of limiting car usage is the reduction in greenhouse gas emissions. Cars are a major contributor to greenhouse gas emissions, which are a leading cause of climate change. By promoting alternatives to driving, such as walking, cycling, and public transportation, communities can reduce their carbon footprint. This is especially important in the United States, where transportation is the second largest source of emissions.

