"Limiting car usage has numerous advantages for both individuals and the environment. The passages provided offer examples of cities and countries that have implemented restrictions on cars, showing the positive outcomes of these measures. By reducing car usage, we can improve air quality, reduce greenhouse gas emissions, and create more livable communities.

