In the German suburb of Vauban, car ownership is allowed but parking is limited to large garages at the edge of the community. As a result, the majority of families in Vauban do not own cars and have embraced the car-free lifestyle. Residents have expressed a sense of relief and happiness, as they no longer have to deal with the stress and tension that comes with car ownership. This highlights another advantage of limiting car usage – it can improve the overall well-being of individuals. Walking, riding bicycles, or taking public transportation can have positive effects on physical health, reducing sedentary lifestyles and fostering a more active and healthy community.

